In re RUSSELL. (City Court of New York,

General Term.

May 29, 1897.) In the matter of Irving L. Bussell, a judgment debtor. Scott & Upson, for appellant. Franklin Bien, for respondent. PEB CUBIAM.

Appeal from an order denying a motion to punish for contempt. An examination of the record satisfies us that the court had jurisdiction of both the subject-matter and of the person of the judgment debtor. The order appealed from must be reversed, with costs.
